We recommend that the Municipal Accountant: 1. Prepare and submit all documents and reports such as duly approved RIS to evidence the issuance of the materials from stock and Report of Supplies and Materials Issued etc. as basis for crediting the non-existing balance from the books; 2. Direct the General Services Officer of the Municipal Treasurer to prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) weekly as a basis by the Accounting Unit in preparing the JEV to record the supplies and materials issued; 3. Adjust the non-existing and consumed unaccounted materials inventory in the books.

We recommend that the Municipal Accountant:
1. Comply with the provisions of Sections 121 of the Manual of the NGAS, Volume I on the proper recording and reporting on issuance of supplies and materials;
2. Restore to inventory accounts the undocumented P1,610,986.66 adjustments; and
3. Maintain the Subsidiary Ledger Card (SLC) for inventories.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor:
a. Require the General Services or the Municipal Treasurer to conduct inventory taking periodically and submit the inventory report for periodic reconciliation of records between the General Services and Accounting Unit;
b. Require the General Services Officer or the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain and update regularly the SCs and SLCs for each inventory item, regularly reconcile their records and immediately effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts and/or supply records for any differences noted;
c. Submit the SSMI and RIS as supporting document to the issuances of inventory as drawn in the general journal;
d. Require the Accounting Office and the signing official in the purchase order, to supply needed information in the disbursement vouchers and purchase orders;
e. Classify and record transactions to appropriate accounts.

