We recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Engineer/BAC Chairman to ensure that:
A list of the  Municipality’s programs/projects and activities, inclusive of those for implementation and non-infrastructure projects is submitted to the Audit Team at the beginning of the year;
Relevant information regarding the PPAs of the Municipality be posted in  signboards or black/bulletin boards  following the provisions of the cited Circular;
The Audit Team be informed that the appropriate project signboards and/or notices have been  posted  within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity; and
Maintain updated Project Status based on the data sourced from the monthly monitoring report prepared by Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the concerned officers of the Municipal Agriculture Office to:

Prepare a detailed and viable project proposals in consideration of (i) standardized screening criteria and process and (ii) minimum training requirements and skills of the recipients;

Encourage the recipients of the Vermi-Production and composting projects to utilize the benefits of SWM by collecting suitable waste for ANC food consumption;

Formalize contract or agreement to designate the obligations and responsibilities of the recipients; and 

Monitor the strict implementation and document the 2-piglet return policy from the recipients for first gestation period of the dispersed sows. 

Further, we recommended that BAC observe the applicable procurement activities for this type of project and submit the lacking supporting documents relevant to the conducted bidding.

